-- HSBC Bank Sells 23 Million Rand of 6.18% Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2012-01-30T15:48:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-30/hsbc-bank-sells-23-million-rand-of-6-18-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:              HSBC Bank plc
Amount:              23 million South African Rand
Coupon:              6.18 percent
Duration:            Four years
Sales period:        Jan. 31 - Feb. 22
Settlement date:     Feb. 24, 2012
Maturity:            Feb. 24, 2016
Uridashi Manager:    SBI Securities Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  